red relevance threshold.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.25,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.6,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"The end-to-end latency from receiving the query to returning re-ranked results stays below 2 seconds for the median case.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"Behavior spans multiple agentic steps in sequence (embedding model call + LLM reranking call) and asserts an end-to-end SLO, so MULTI-STEP applies. Real network/service latency and inter-stage orchestration dominate this failure mode; stubs can mask true median latency (REAL-INFRA + MOCK-HIDE). Rejected Agentic-only: a single-model test cannot capture cross-stage pipeline timing budget allocation required by the behavior text.","test_description":"Execute production-like end-to-end search requests through the full pipeline (real embedding + vector search + real LLM rerank), collect latency distribution, and assert median response time is under 2.0s.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.03,"System":0.22,"Agentic":0.2,"Workflow":0.55}}]}
